		<div class="post" id="post-2061940">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2061940)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2061940">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/procyonlotor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(778357); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=778357&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183102" alt="ProcyonLotor" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=778357)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/procyonlotor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(778357); return false;" >ProcyonLotor</a></span> <span class="odate time_1404258472 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Jul 2014 23:47</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2061940">
									

<p>Again, might as well just copy-and-paste this at the front of each of my comments of yours: you're probably the best character writer on this site, and it shows in this piece. You managed to make all the different sects distinct and unique in a short period of time, which was well done, and the ending was perfectly executed as well (although the letter felt a bit Hallmark-schmaltzy).<br />
Only complaints are small ones: the first letter didn't quite sound like it was written by a nine-year-old, foremost. Splitting hairs, but when you're going for such a distinctive voice such as that, accuracy is important. You probably could have made the schism feel more bitter as well. I was raised on one side of the Catholic/Protestant schism, and know many on the other side, and that is still something that people almost come to blows over. Obviously, you didn't have a lot of space to put 30 years of harsh religious debate into, and for the most part you did a fine job, but there could have been just a bit more to the emotional crux of it.<br />
Overall, however, it's an excellent character piece, and reads about as believably as is possible for the subject matter. Very well done.</p>

							</div>

								
					
